en_817633_0	Speaker Karu Jayasuriya had agreed to provide parliamentary privileges to newly appointed Prime Minister Mahinda Rajapaksa.
en_817633_1	The Speaker has taken this decision following an intimation made to him by President Maithripala Sirisena.
en_817633_2	A meeting between the President and the Speaker was held yesterday.
en_817633_3	Several matters were discussed at this meeting.
en_817633_4	The President drew the attention of the Speaker for the provision of facilities accorded to the new Prime Minister within Parliament.
en_817633_5	The Speaker had mentioned that officials in Parliament were working in accordance to the gazette notification issued by the President on the appointment of a new Prime Minister.
